@UNBAN\_SHAHRAZAD: actually, [Ruby Medallion](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ruby Medallion) works with [Fireball](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Fireball), since it (like other cost reducers) applies to the total mana cost, which includes the number chosen for X.


As an example, you control 6 untapped lands and a [Ruby Medallion](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ruby Medallion), and are about to throw a [Fireball](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Fireball) at your opponent's smug face. You announce X as 6, making the total mana cost {6}{R}, which is then reduced to {5}{R} by the medallion. Finally, you tap your 6 untapped lands and pay the now reduced cost, turning that smug look into a frown.


The same thing is true with [Training Grounds](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Training Grounds), except you cannot reduce the cost below {1} (Though you may still choose to redirect only 1 or 2 damage, it'll still cost {1}, just like redirecting 3 damage)
